history''. Duke University Press. '''32''' (1): 37\u201362. ISSN 0014-1801. {{JSTOR|482092}}. {{OCLC|478130795}}. Retrieved 2017-06-27. {{via|[[JSTOR]]}}\n:Garc\u00eda A\u00f1overos, Jes\u00fas Mar\u00eda (1988). \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20170327171321/https://dialnet.unirioja.es/descarga/articulo/4007895.pdf Presencia franciscana en la Taguzgalpa y la Tologalpa (la Mosquitia)]\". ''Mesoam\u00e9rica''. Antigua Guatemala: El Centro de Investigaciones Regionales de Mesoam\u00e9rica (CIRMA) in conjunction with Plumsock Mesoamerican Studies, South Woodstock, Vermont, US. '''9''': 47\u201378. ISSN 0252-9963. {{OCLC|7141215}}. Archived from [https://dialnet.unirioja.es/descarga/articulo/4007895.pdf the original] on 2017-03-27. {{in lang|es}}\n:Garc\u00eda Buchard, Ethel. ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20120308192514/http://www.ciicla.ucr.ac.cr/revista_intercambio/001_001/005.pdf Evangelizar a los indios gentiles de la Frontera de Honduras: una ardua tarea (Siglos XVII-XIX)]'' (in Spanish). San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica: Centro de Investigaci\u00f3n en Identidad y Cultura Latinoamericanas (CIICLA), Universidad de Costa Rica. Archived from [http://www.ciicla.ucr.ac.cr/revista_intercambio/001_001/005.pdf the original] on 2012-03-08.\n:Grenke, Arthur (2005). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=iBaGO8Ue2NMC&pg=PA142 God, Greed, and Genocide: The Holocaust Through the Centuries]''. Washington, DC, US: New Academia Publishing. {{ISBN|0-9767042-0-X}}. {{OCLC|255346071}}.\n:Healy, Paul (2006) [1980]. [https://muse.jhu.edu/chapter/1554937 A Brief History of the Culture Subarea] in ''[https://muse.jhu.edu/book/40357 Archaeology of the Rivas Region, Nicaragua]''. pp. 19\u201334. Waterloo, Ontario, Canada: Wilfrid Laurier University Press. {{ISBN|0-88920-094-7}}. {{via|[[Project MUSE]]}}\n:Ibarra Rojas, Eugenia (1994). \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20170726104807/http://biblioteca.museocostarica.go.cr/volumen.aspx?id=3456 Los Matagalpas a principios del siglo XVI: aproximaci\u00f3n a las relaciones inter\u00e9tnicas en Nicaragua (1552\u20131581)]\". ''V\u00ednculos''. '''18\u201319''' (1\u20132): 229\u2013243. San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica: Museo Nacional de Costa Rica. ISSN  0304-3703. Archived from [http://biblioteca.museocostarica.go.cr/volumen.aspx?id=3456 the original] on 2017-07-26. {{in lang|es}}.\n:Ibarra Rojas, Eugenia (2001). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=IAcx6DtZba4C Fronteras \u00e9tnicas en la conquista de Nicaragua y Nicoya: Entre la solidaridad y el conflicto 800 d.C.-1544]''. San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica: Editorial de la Universidad de Costa Rica. {{ISBN|9977-67-685-2}}. {{OCLC|645912024}}. {{in lang|es}}\n:Leonard, Thomas M. (2011). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=526qA6ckcZ4C The History of Honduras]''. Santa Barbara, California, US: ABC-CLIO. {{ISBN|978-0-313-36303-0}}. {{OCLC|701322740}}. {{via|[[Questia]]}}\n:Mel\u00e9ndez, Carlos (1976) ''[http://www.enriquebolanos.org/data/media/book/CCBA_-_SERIE_HISTORICA_-_09_-_Hernandez_de_Co%CC%81rdoba.pdf Hern\u00e1ndez de C\u00f3rdoba: Capit\u00e1n de conquista en Nicaragua]''. Managua, Nicaragua: Editorial San Jos\u00e9. Serie hist\u00f3rica 9. {{OCLC|538851181}}. {{in lang|es}}\n:Mena Garc\u00eda, Mar\u00eda del Carmen (1992) ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=o9qselEBMysC Pedrarias D\u00e1vila o \"la ira de Dios\": una historia olvidada]''. Sevilla, Spain: Universidad de Sevilla. {{ISBN|84-7405-834-1}}. {{in lang|es}}\n:Merril, Tim (1993a). \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20161113225835/http://countrystudies.us/nicaragua/20.htm Geography]\" in ''[http://countrystudies.us/nicaragua/ Nicaragua: A Country Study]''. Washington, D. C., US: GPO for the Library of Congress. Accessed on 2017-07-11. Archived from [http://countrystudies.us/nicaragua/20.htm the original] on 2017-11-13.\n:Montoya, Ramiro (2015). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=Z9brCQAAQBAJ Cr\u00f3nicas del oro y la plata amerinanos]''. Madrid, Spain: Visi\u00f3n Libros. {{ISBN|978-84-16284-31-3}}. {{OCLC|952956657}}. {{in lang|es}}\n:Nessler, Graham T. (2016). ''[https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=q2I3CwAAQBAJ An Islandwide Struggle for Freedom: Revolution, Emancipation, and Reenslavement in Hispaniola 1789\u20131809]''. Chapel Hill, North Carolina, US: University of North Carolina Press. {{ISBN|978-1-4696-2687-1}}. {{OCLC|945632920}}.\n:Newson, Linda (November 1982). \"[https://www.jstor.org/stable/156458  The Depopulation of Nicaragua in the Sixteenth Century]\". ''Journal of Latin American Studies''. Cambridge University Press. '''14''' (2): 253\u2013286. ISSN 0022-216X. {{JSTOR|156458}}. {{OCLC|4669522494}}. Retrieved 2017-07-04. {{via|[[JSTOR]]}}\n:Olson, James S.; Sam L. Slick; Samuel Freeman; Virginia Garrard Burnett; Fred Koestler (1992) \"[https://www.questia.com/read/28625075/historical-dictionary-of-the-spanish-empire-1402-1975 Historical Dictionary of the Spanish Empire, 1402\u20131975]\". New York, US: Greenwood Press. {{ISBN|0-313-26413-9}}. {{via|[[Questia]]}}\n:Orellano, Jorge Eduardo (1979) \"[https://www.jstor.org/stable/25661767 Oviedo y la provincia de Nicaragua]\". Anuario de Estudios Centroamericanos. San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica: Universidad de Costa Rica. 15: 125\u2013129. {{JSTOR|25661767}}. {{via|[[JSTOR]]}} {{in lang|es}}\n:Pohl, John; Hook, Adam (2008) [2001]. ''The Conquistador 1492\u20131550''. Warrior. 40. Oxford, UK and New York, US: Osprey Publishing. {{ISBN|978-1-84176-175-6}}. {{OCLC|47726663}}.\n:Polo Sifontes, Francis (1986). ''Los Cakchiqueles en la Conquista de Guatemala'' (in Spanish). Guatemala City, Guatemala: CENALTEX. {{OCLC|82712257}}.\n:Quir\u00f3s Vargas, Claudia; and Margarita Bola\u00f1os Arqu\u00edn (1989) \"[https://www.jstor.org/stable/25661952 Una reinterpretaci\u00f3n del origen de la dominaci\u00f3n colonial espa\u00f1ola en Costa Rica: 1510\u20131569]\". ''Anuario de Estudios Centroamericanos''. San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica: Universidad de Costa Rica. '''15''' (1): 29\u201348. {{JSTOR|25661952}}. {{via|[[JSTOR]]}