Tucan]]\n| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\" align=\"center\" |[[Great green macaw|Plough ambiguous]]\n| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\" align=\"center\" |[[Harpy eagle|Harpia harpyja]]\n| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\" align=\"center\" |[[White-crowned parrot|Pionus senilis]]\n\n|}\n</div>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[:Category:National parks of Honduras]]\n* [[Agriculture of Honduras]]\n* [[R\u00edo Pl\u00e1tano Biosphere Reserve|Reservation of the Biosphere of River Banana]]\n* [[La Tigra National Park|National park The Tigra]]\n* [[Lancetilla|Botanic garden Lancetilla]]\n* [[Ecology of Honduras]]\n* [[Geography of Honduras]]\n* [[Climate of Honduras]]\n* [[Geography of Honduras]]\n* [[List of national parks of Honduras]]\n* [[Education in Honduras]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Decree No. 104-93 issued by the Sovereign [[National Congress of Honduras]]  (consulted 2012).[https://web.archive.org/web/20140502033354/http://www.honduraseducacional.com/Leyes/LeyGeneraldelAmbiente.pdf]\n* '''General law of the Environment and General Regulation of the Environment''', Office of the Environment, Publisher Guaymuras; Honduras, 1995.\n* Database biodiversity in Honduras Wild Honduras  (consulted 2012).[http://www.hondurassilvestre.com/]\n* Decree No. 104-93 issued by the Sovereign [[National Congress of Honduras]]  (consulted 2012).[https://web.archive.org/web/20140502033354/http://www.honduraseducacional.com/Leyes/LeyGeneraldelAmbiente.pdf]\n* '''General law of the Environment and General Regulation of the Environment''', Office of the Environment, Publisher Guaymuras; Honduras, 1995.\n* Database biodiversity in Honduras Wild Honduras  (consulted 2012).[http://www.hondurassilvestre.com/]\n\n[[Category:Fauna of Honduras| ]]\n[[Category:Flora of Honduras| ]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toLa Mosquitia(link changed toLa Mosquitia (Honduras)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flora_and_Fauna_of_Honduras"}
{"title_page": "Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        = Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio em \u201cAventuras com Tio Maneco\u201d.tif\n| name         = Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1934|10|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| occupation   = Actor, film director, screenwriter\n| yearsactive  = 1958-present\n}}\n\n'''Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio''' (born 15 October 1934) is a Brazilian actor, [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]]. He has appeared in more than 80 films and television shows since 1958. His 1962 film ''[[The Beggars (film)|The Beggars]]'' was entered into the [[3rd Moscow International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Moscow1963\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1963 |title=3rd Moscow International Film Festival (1963) |accessdate=30 November 2012 |work=MIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116210707/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1963 |archivedate=16 January 2013  }}</ref> His elder sister [[Dirce Migliaccio]] was also an actress.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[The Beggars (film)|The Beggars]]'' (1962)\n* ''[[My Home Is Copacabana]]'' (1965)\n* ''[[The Hour and Turn of Augusto Matraga]]'' (1965)\n* ''[[Entranced Earth]]'' (1967)\n* ''[[Pra Quem Fica, Tchau]]'' (1971)\n* ''[[Tanga (film)|Tanga]]'' (1987)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0585919|Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio}}\n\n{{Trof\u00e9u Oscarito}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Migliaccio, Flavio}}\n[[Category:1934 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Male actors from S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n\n\n{{Brazil-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        = Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio em \u201cAventuras com Tio Maneco\u201d.tif\n| name         = Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1934|10|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| occupation   = Actor, film director, screenwriter\n| yearsactive  = 1958-present\n}}\n\n'''Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio''' (born 15 October 1934) is a Brazilian actor, [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]]. He has appeared in more than 80 films and television shows since 1958. His 1962 film ''[[The Beggars (film)|The Beggars]]'' was entered into the [[3rd Moscow International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Moscow1963\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1963 |title=3rd Moscow International Film Festival (1963) |accessdate=30 November 2012 |work=MIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116210707/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1963 |archivedate=16 January 2013  }}</ref> His elder sister [[Dirce Migliaccio]] was also an actress.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[The Beggars (film)|The Beggars]]'' (1962)\n* ''[[My Home Is Copacabana]]'' (1965)\n* ''[[The Hour and Turn of Augusto Matraga]]'' (1965)\n* ''[[Entranced Earth]]'' (1967)\n* ''[[Pra Quem Fica, Tchau]]'' (1971)\n* ''[[Tanga (film)|Tanga]]'' (1987)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0585919|Fl\u00e1vio Migliaccio}}\n\n{{Trof\u00e9u Oscarito}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Migliaccio, Flavio}}\n[[Category:1934 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n[[Category:Brazilian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Male actors from S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n\n\n{{Brazil-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fl%C3%A1vio_Migliaccio"}
